<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-28-0393 </DOCNO><TEXT>In a process for the treatment of stack gases, particularly from coal-firedpower stations, with NO/sub x/ and SO/sub x/ contents at temperatureslower than 150/sup 0/C, a solution is to be created in which the harmfulsubstances NO/sub x/ and SO/sub x/ are removed from the waste gases witha high yield, particularly at temperatures below 150/sup 0/C. This isachieved by reducing NO/sub x/ catalytically (dry) in a first step andby converting SO/sub x/ to gypsum (wet) in a second step.</TEXT></DOC>